## Authorization (internal/authz)

### Permission Checking

Use authz helpers for role-based access control:

```go
import "github.com/cmelgarejo/go-modulith-template/internal/authz"

func (s *Service) DeleteUser(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteUserRequest) (*pb.DeleteUserResponse, error) {
    // Require specific permission
    if err := authz.RequirePermission(ctx, authz.PermissionUsersDelete); err != nil {
        return nil, errors.ToGRPC(err)
    }

    // Or require role
    if err := authz.RequireRole(ctx, "admin", "moderator"); err != nil {
        return nil, errors.ToGRPC(err)
    }

    // Or require ownership
    if err := authz.RequireOwnership(ctx, req.UserId); err != nil {
        return nil, errors.ToGRPC(err)
    }

    // Or ownership OR role
    if err := authz.RequireOwnershipOrRole(ctx, req.UserId, "admin"); err != nil {
        return nil, errors.ToGRPC(err)
    }

    // ... business logic
}
```

### Custom Roles & Permissions

Define custom roles for your module:

```go
import "github.com/cmelgarejo/go-modulith-template/internal/authz"

func init() {
    authz.RegisterRole("moderator", []authz.Permission{
        "posts:delete",
        "comments:delete",
        "users:ban",
    })
}
```

### Built-in Permissions

- `authz.PermissionUsersRead`
- `authz.PermissionUsersWrite`
- `authz.PermissionUsersDelete`
- `authz.PermissionAdminAll` (wildcard for admins)
